# shadcn/ui & styling

- Config: `components.json` — style `new-york`, CSS in `src/css/globals.css`
- **MCP**: use shadcn MCP tools to search registries, view examples, and get add commands before writing custom UI
- Add components: MCP `get_add_command_for_items` → run command; fallback: `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`
- Merge classes with `cn()` from `src/lib/utils`

```tsx
import { cn } from 'src/lib/utils'
<Button className={cn('mt-4', className)} />
```

- Tailwind v4: tokens defined in `@theme` / `@theme inline` in `globals.css`
- Dark mode: `ThemeProvider` toggles `.dark` on `<html>`; use `dark:` variants
- Button has custom variants (`lightprimary`, `outlinesuccess`, etc.) — reuse before adding new ones
- Icons: Lucide in ui components; Solar/Iconify (`solar:*`) in layout and sidebar

Do not edit generated ui files for one-off styling — pass `className` or wrap in a shared component.
